.TH VV 1 "2026-03-08" "vv 0.7.1-8-g8fdfa97" "Vibe-Vault Manual"
.SH NAME
vv \- vibe\-vault session capture
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B vv
.I command
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B vv
(vibe-vault) captures Claude Code session transcripts as structured
Obsidian notes with frontmatter metadata, project context documents,
and Dataview dashboards.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B "vv init [path] [\-\-git]"
Create a new vault (default: ./vibe\-vault)
.TP
.B "vv hook [install | ...]"
Hook mode (reads stdin from Claude Code)
.TP
.B "vv context [init | ...]"
Manage vault\-resident AI context
.TP
.B "vv process <file.jsonl>"
Process a single transcript file
.TP
.B "vv index"
Rebuild session index from notes
.TP
.B "vv backfill [path]"
Discover and process historical transcripts
.TP
.B "vv archive"
Compress transcripts into vault archive
.TP
.B "vv reprocess [\-\-project X]"
Re\-generate notes from transcripts
.TP
.B "vv check"
Validate config, vault, and hook setup
.TP
.B "vv stats [\-\-project X]"
Show session analytics and metrics
.TP
.B "vv friction [\-\-project X]"
Show friction analysis and correction patterns
.TP
.B "vv trends [\-\-project X]"
Show metric trends over time
.TP
.B "vv inject [\-\-project X]"
Output session\-start context payload
.TP
.B "vv export [\-\-format X]"
Export session data (JSON or CSV)
.TP
.B "vv mcp"
Start MCP server (JSON\-RPC over stdio)
.TP
.B "vv templates [list | ...]"
Inspect, compare, and reset vault templates
.TP
.B "vv version"
Print version
.SH CONFIGURATION
Configuration file: ~/.config/vibe-vault/config.toml
